Two series of premaxillary teeth. Teeth of outer series tricuspid, smaller than inner series, numbering 3 to 5 . Five teeth, pentacuspid, in inner series. One or two maxillary teeth; anterior teeth tricuspidate, and second tooth, when present, smaller and conical. Four or five anterior large, pentacuspid, dentary teeth posteriorly followed by slightly smaller and usually tricuspid teeth, and 4 to 10 much smaller ones, conical (
Fig. 2
).
